GateDocument.TextWithNodes: * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * CALL FOR PAPERS : - DNIS 2000 * * International Workshop on * * Databases in Networked Information Systems * * * * December 4 - 6 , 2000 * * University of Aizu , Aizu- Wakamatsu city * * JAPAN * * * * http : / / www . u-aizu . ac . jp / labs / sw-db / DNIS 2000 * * * * Submission Deadline : June 1 , 2000 * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * COSPONSORED BY : Department of Computer Software , University of Aizu The DNIS 2000 workshop will focus on infrastructure for information management . Database Systems are likely to play a central role in the evolving information systems . It aims at promoting research related to - * Managing components , and application services , * Distributed client / middle-ware / server computing , * XML , E- commerce , * Using core technologies for the new applications , * Databases in modern architectures ( middle-ware , mobile , the WEB ) , * integration of technologies Current research activity on - Algorithms for collecting , analyzing , and securing data for decision support ; Integrating advanced technologies for automating C 2 B and B 2 B e-commerce , dynamic workflow , and supply chain management ; Approaches and algorithms for automatic data warehouse administration ; Architectures for simplifying the access to and querying of heterogeneous information sources ; - - and in addition , all aspects of data management for Information Systems are sought for participation . The workshop will offer a programme with contributed papers and participation from invited speakers . The workshop plans to publish its proceedings in the Springer Lecture Notes in Computer Science ( LNCS ) } series . Contributions should cover concepts for implementation , management of meta -data , systems architecture and experience gained in Information Systems and DBMSs . Broad categories for additional topics are : o Design and implementation of o Architectures Information Systems - information systems in health care - distributed architectures - teleinformatics - operating system interaction - emerging technologies for geo-based - storage architectures applications - garbage collection - conceptual or logical models for - mobile computing systems spatio-temporal processes o Inter-operability o Application systems - database systems - Data Management in telecommunications - semi-structured data - high-speed networks - the WWW - data security Tentative Schedule includes Invited Talks by : U . Dayal , D . Agarwal , K . Ramamritham Grants : Limited travel and support grants are available for paper presenters based on submission of grant request application to local funding agencies . Please contact the workshop organizers for details . A detailed CV , an abstract of the presentation during the workshop , and the cost to be covered by the grant have to be communicated by the candidates . The requests for grant applications should be sent as early as possible .
